content:
when you're looking to make the most with what little you have starting out, it's best to analyze your team on which cards are your main damage sources - level those up first

for your first few weeks it's good to get a single team in decent condition but after that it's prudent to get everyone you have to level 60 at least, even with just lackluster skill levels (mainly for dtide, getting 300 is easy with a level 60 only team because you'll eclipse the enemy in stats)

and after that it just depends really, do you want to push further into story (both normal and hard mode)? or do you want to push your dtide score so you can tap into the limit break materials sooner?
